frame0.consensus_text: In <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> old Baily ended on tuesday night when only one man Rec<sw-ex>eive</sw-ex>d Sentence of death
for Burglary 9 burned in <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Cheek some ordered to be whipt & others into her
Mai<sw-ex>es</sw-ex>tyes Service & one Bowen who was some Months past Convicted of Murder
but obtained a Reprive was called down to his former Sentence & ordered to
Prepare for death. <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Alteration that is Made in <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Bill for Recruiting her
such as have not a sufficient Maintenance shall be Impressable & this Alteration
Propositions made to him by <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> marquis de
Prie & <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> Gen<sw-ex>era</sw-ex>ll Thaun is to continue at at<brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl>
orders
They Write from Vienna of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> 12 <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl>
Treaty with <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Court of Rome is as good as at a
stand <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Pope endeavouring to play <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Fox
by amusing <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Court to gaine time & to <brev-y>th</brev-y><sw-ex>a</sw-ex><sl>t</sl> end
amongst other things insists that <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Duke
of Modena according to his example Should
disband <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> 7000 men which he has on
ffort but <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Emperor is resolved not to
abandone <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Intrest of that Prince but to
Support his iust Right to Camachio & <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl>
Ferrarez upon which Count Thaun has
orders sent him to march directly to Rome
as has <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Prince of Darmstadt on <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl>
side of Naples to Compell <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Pontiff to a
Complyance who tis given out will retire
& leave Rome to <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Government of a Legat
<brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Marshall de Teste & <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Ministers of king
Philip labour all they can by threats
& promises to keep Clement <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> XI from an
accomodation -
The Confederates in Poland are resolved
not to own king Stanislaus but to recall
King Augustus upon advice of which <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl>
King of Sweeden is resolved to returne
With his Army into Poland which consists but
of <sw-unclear>22000</sw-unclear> men <sw-unclear>800</sw-unclear> of which are sick and
daily harrassed on every side by <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> fforces
of <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Czar & if we may credit our letters
has hapned between both armys in which
the Sweeds were totaly routed but this wants
Conformation - <brev-y>th</brev-y><sl>e</sl> Czar Invites King Augustus
to return to Poland.
